---
layout: page.njk
title: James Nash on the Blog
description: Blog posts by James Nash. Mostly musings and ramblings about mobile phone technology.
keywords:
  - feed
  - twitter
  - mobile
  - technology
  - web
  - geek
eleventyNavigation:
  key: Blog
  order: 2
  titleAttr: James Nash on the Blog
pagination:
  data: "collections.blog"
  size: 5
  alias: 'blogPosts'
  reverse: true
permalink: "blog/{% if pagination.pageNumber > 0 %}page-{{ pagination.pageNumber + 1 }}/{% endif %}"
---
{% from 'partials/archive-nav.njk' import archiveNav %}
{% set firstPage = {
  url: pagination.href.first if (pagination.href.first != page.url),
  label: 'Page 1'
} %}
{% set prevPage = {
  url: pagination.href.previous,
  label: 'Page ' + (pagination.pageNumber) if pagination.href.previous else 'N/A'
} %}
{% set nextPage = {
  url: pagination.href.next,
  label: 'Page ' + (pagination.pageNumber + 2) if pagination.href.next else 'N/A'
} %}
{% set lastPage = {
  url: pagination.href.last if (pagination.href.last != page.url),
  label: 'Page ' + pagination.pages.length
} %}

<div id="main-content">
{% for blogPost in blogPosts %}
  <div class="box">
    <h2><a href="{{ blogPost.url }}">{{ blogPost.data.title }}</a></h2>
    <p>Posted on {% humanDate blogPost.date %}</p>
  </div>
{% endfor %}
</div>

<div id="secondary-content">
  <div class="box">
    <h2>Browse the blog</h2>
    <p>You are on page {{ pagination.pageNumber + 1 }} of {{ pagination.pages.length }}</p>
    {{ archiveNav(null, firstPage, prevPage, nextPage, lastPage) | safe }}
  </div>

  <div class="box">
    <h2>Elsewhere</h2>
    <p>I have also blogged elsewhere over the years:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><a href="https://medium.com/@cirrus" rel="me">My Medium blog</a>. Mostly stuff I write about relating to my work on design systems and web development.</li>
        <li>I've published a few posts on the Wipro Digital blog:
            <ul>
                <li><a href="https://wiprodigital.com/2015/07/07/series-weaving-a-better-web-part-1-of-2/">Weaving a Better Web (Part 1 of 2)</a>, 7. July 2015</li>
                <li><a href="https://wiprodigital.com/2015/07/14/series-weaving-a-better-web-part-2-of-2/">Weaving a Better Web (Part 2 of 2)</a>, 14. July 2015</li>
                <li><a href="https://wiprodigital.com/2015/08/20/whats-your-url-strategy/">What's Your URL Strategy?</a>, 20. August 2015</li>
                <li><a href="https://wiprodigital.com/2016/03/17/implementing-atomic-design-at-wipro-digital/">Implementing Atomic Design at Wipro Digital</a>, 17. March 2016</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>Some really old stuff I did while working at Symbian:
            <ul>
                <li><a href="https://smartphoneshow.wordpress.com/">Symbian Smartphone Show Blog</a>. Coverage of the 2008 Smartphone Show.</li>
                <li><a href="https://symbianmwc08.wordpress.com/">Symbian @ MWC 2008</a>. Coverage of the 2008 Mobile World Congress.</li>
                <li><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20110202185319/http://blog.symbian.org/">Symbian Foundation Blog</a>. (Now defunct. I wrote some of the original posts when the blog started and also created the <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20090405043504/http://blog.symbian.org:80/2009/04/01/symbian-based-toaster-announced/">Symbian Toaster April Fool's</a>)</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>
